Verilator 5.029 devel rev v5.028-137-g811eab8fa
```

Hello. I found a bug where non-blocking assignments don't work as intended at the end of an always block.

```systemverilog
// tb.sv
module tb;

int delay = 0; always #1 delay = int'($time) / 4;
task automatic do_delay;
    if (delay > 0) #(delay);
endtask

// `a` should match `b`
logic a = 0;
always begin
    a <= 1;
    do_delay();
    a <= 0;

    #1;
end

logic b = 0;
always begin
    b <= 1;
    do_delay();
    b <= 0;

    #1;
    b <= 1; // this line should do nothing
end

always #1 assert (a == b);

initial begin
    $dumpfile("dump.vcd");
    $dumpvars;
    #20;
    $finish;
end

endmodule
```
```
// verilator.f
tb.sv
--binary
--trace
--assert
```

In simulation, `a` does not match `b` when the `do_delay()` task does not create a delay:

![gtkwave](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/75e89a80-7534-4922-8874-274f32cd1749)

I won't have time to look into this for awhile.
